  "articleSummary": "**Summary**\n\n\"Into the Breach\" is a technical analysis and defensive guide addressing the evolving landscape of developer-targeted supply chain attacks and credential theft. The article argues that the traditional \"local is safe\" development model is obsolete, reframing the developer's workstation as a \"credential warehouse\" vulnerable to prompt injection, malicious packages, and infostealers like Lumma. Adopting an authoritative yet practical tone, the author advocates for a \"defense-in-depth\" strategy that replaces human vigilance with structural boundaries. Key technical recommendations include isolating development environments using DevContainers, deploying Canarytokens as digital tripwires, and implementing strict filesystem mount limits to contain potential breaches.",
